---
title: "Extra repayments & offset calculator"
description: "See how extra home loan repayments or an offset account balance could cut years off your mortgage and save you serious interest — with charts that show the gap."
layout: base.njk
permalink: /calculators/extra-repayments/
---

{% block schema %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "Extra Repayments & Offset Calculator",
  "description": "{{ description }}",
  "url": "https://wombathomeloans.com.au/calculators/extra-repayments/",
  "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Web",
  "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "AUD" },
  "provider": { "@type": "MortgageBroker", "name": "Wombat Home Loans", "url": "https://wombathomeloans.com.au/" }
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

<section class="section section--tight">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="calc-breadcrumb"><a href="/calculators/">← All calculators</a></p>
    <span class="eyebrow">Extra repayments &amp; offset</span>
    <h1>The quiet superpower of <em>Australian mortgages.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Every dollar above the minimum — paid in extra, or parked in an offset account — attacks the principal directly. The effect compounds for decades, and it's usually the cheapest "investment return" you'll ever get: your mortgage rate, tax-free.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--cool section--tight" data-calc="extra">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="calc-grid">

      {# ── Inputs ── #}
      <div class="calc-card calc-panel">

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="e-amount-input">Loan balance</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="e-amount-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Loan balance in dollars">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="e-amount" type="range" min="50000" max="3000000" step="10000" value="600000" aria-label="Loan balance slider">
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="e-rate">Interest rate</label>
            <span class="calc-field__value" id="e-rate-out"></span>
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="e-rate" type="range" min="3" max="10" step="0.05" value="5.75">
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="e-term">Years remaining</label>
            <span class="calc-field__value" id="e-term-out"></span>
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="e-term" type="range" min="1" max="40" step="1" value="28">
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="e-extra-input">Extra repayment (per month)</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="e-extra-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Extra monthly repayment">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="e-extra" type="range" min="0" max="5000" step="50" value="500" aria-label="Extra repayment slider">
          <p class="calc-field__hint">Even $100 a month makes a visible dent — try it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="e-offset-input">Offset account balance</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="e-offset-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Offset account balance">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="e-offset" type="range" min="0" max="500000" step="5000" value="20000" aria-label="Offset balance slider">
          <p class="calc-field__hint">Money in an offset reduces the balance interest is charged on — while staying available whenever you need it. We assume it stays put for the life of the loan.</p>
        </div>

      </div>

      {# ── Results ── #}
      <div class="stack-lg">

        <div class="calc-card">
          <div class="calc-hero-stat">
            <span class="calc-hero-stat__label">Interest you'd save</span>
            <span class="calc-hero-stat__value" id="e-hero">$0</span>
            <p class="calc-hero-stat__note" id="e-hero-note"></p>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-stats">
            <div class="calc-stat">
              <span class="calc-stat__label">Mortgage-free</span>
              <span class="calc-stat__value" id="e-stat-time">—</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-stat">
              <span class="calc-stat__label">New payoff time</span>
              <span class="calc-stat__value" id="e-stat-payoff">—</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-stat">
              <span class="calc-stat__label">Interest — minimum only</span>
              <span class="calc-stat__value" id="e-stat-base-int">$0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-stat">
              <span class="calc-stat__label">Interest — your plan</span>
              <span class="calc-stat__value" id="e-stat-new-int">$0</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-card">
          <h3>Two futures, one loan</h3>
          <p class="calc-field__hint" style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);">The dotted line is coasting on minimum repayments. The solid line is you, with a plan. The gap between them is your money.</p>
          <div class="calc-chart"><canvas id="e-chart-balance" role="img" aria-label="Line chart comparing loan balance over time with and without extra repayments and offset"></canvas></div>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-card">
          <h3>Total interest, side by side</h3>
          <div class="calc-chart calc-chart--short"><canvas id="e-chart-interest" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart comparing total interest with and without extra repayments"></canvas></div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-assumptions" data-reveal>
      <details>
        <summary>Assumptions behind this calculator</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>The interest rate stays constant, repayments are monthly, and the extra amount is paid every month from now until the loan is cleared.</li>
          <li>The offset balance stays constant for the life of the loan (in reality it moves around — this is a "steady state" picture).</li>
          <li>No fees, no redraws, and no rate changes are modelled. Fixed-rate loans often cap extra repayments — variable loans generally don't.</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% include "calc-cta.njk" %}

{% block scripts %}
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/4.4.1/chart.umd.min.js" defer></script>
<script src="/assets/js/calculators.js?v=20260708-2" defer></script>
{% endblock %}
